

I’ll group it into: **shared screens**, **USER flow screens**, **MANAGER flow screens**, and a couple of optional nice-to-haves.

---

## Shared screens (both USER + MANAGER)

### 1) Splash / Boot screen

**Why:** you need a place to load token + decide where to go (login vs app).
**Does:** checks if token exists, reads role + plantIds, routes accordingly.
**APIs:** none (local storage only).

### 2) Login screen

**Why:** entry point for both roles.
**Does:** email/password login, stores JWT + user info.
**API:** `POST /auth/login`

### 3) Plant selection screen

**Why:** all mobile flows depend on a `plantId`. Users/managers can have multiple plantIds.
**Does:** show plants user has access to; user picks one as “active plant”.
**APIs (2 ways):**

* Preferred: `GET /plants` (show plant names from DB)
* Or fallback: decode plantIds from token and show only IDs (not great UX)

> For manager: this is essential if they manage multiple plants.
> For user: if only 1 plant, you can auto-select and skip this screen.

---

## USER screens (form filling + my submissions)

### 4) Home / Published forms list

**Why:** user needs to see what forms are available for their plant.
**Does:** lists latest published templates; tap to open and fill.
**API:** `GET /mobile/forms?plantId=...`

### 5) Form fill screen (dynamic renderer)

**Why:** this is the core product: render fields dynamically from template metadata.
**Does:** shows fields (TEXT/NUMBER/CHECKBOX/DROPDOWN/DATE/PHOTO), validates locally, prepares answers payload.
**APIs:**

* uses template data already fetched from #4
* for photo upload (inside this screen): `POST /files/upload?folder=photos`
* for final submit: `POST /mobile/forms/submissions`

### 6) Submission success screen (or modal)

**Why:** user needs confirmation + next action (back to list / view submission).
**Does:** show submission id/status + primary actions.
**APIs:** none (uses response from submit).

### 7) My submissions list

**Why:** user needs history + status tracking.
**Does:** list their submissions, filter by status (SUBMITTED/APPROVED/REJECTED), search optional.
**API:** `GET /mobile/forms/submissions/mine?status=...`

### 8) My submission detail

**Why:** user wants to open what they submitted, and see review outcome/reject reason.
**Does:** shows template title + answers + review status + reject reason.
**APIs:**

* `GET /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}`
* for photos: `GET /files/signed-url?key=photos/...`

---

## MANAGER screens (review submissions)

### 9) Review queue screen (submissions list)

**Why:** manager’s main job is to review incoming submissions for their plant(s).
**Does:** shows submissions filtered to manager’s plantIds; default view should be “SUBMITTED”. Add filters: plant, status, search.
**API:** `GET /mobile/forms/submissions`

* Manager will typically call with:

  * `plantId=...` (if plant selected)
  * `status=SUBMITTED` (or rely on default behavior you already coded)

### 10) Review submission detail

**Why:** manager must inspect answers + photos before making a decision.
**Does:** shows enriched submission (template + field metadata) and answers; view photo; show approve/reject actions.
**APIs:**

* `GET /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}`
* `GET /files/signed-url?key=photos/...`

### 11) Reject reason screen (small modal/screen)

**Why:** rejection needs a reason (your backend supports `reason`).
**Does:** collect reason text, submit reject.
**API:** `POST /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}/reject` with `{ reason }`

### 12) Approve confirm (modal)

**Why:** approvals should be deliberate (avoid accidental taps).
**Does:** confirm action and call approve.
**API:** `POST /mobile/forms/submissions/{id}/approve`

### 13) Review history screen (optional but useful)

**Why:** managers often need to see what happened after review, not only pending.
**Does:** same as review queue but status filter defaults to APPROVED/REJECTED.
**API:** `GET /mobile/forms/submissions?status=APPROVED` and `...REJECTED`

> You can merge 9 + 13 into one screen with tabs: Pending | Approved | Rejected.

---

## Shared utility screens (optional but practical)

### 14) Profile / Logout

**Why:** show logged-in user + role + active plant; logout.
**Does:** clear token, go to login.
**APIs:** none.

### 15) Photo viewer screen (optional)

**Why:** better UX for photos (zoom/rotate).
**Does:** open a signed URL in an image viewer.
**API:** uses already-fetched signed url (or calls `GET /files/signed-url` when opening).

